\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult or look after them in other ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Dressing and eating for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
Yes, yes. Oh yes, when that little sister died I'm afraid she was very spoilt because she was younger than the others, she was a lovely little girl, she 
wouldn't go to sleep unless I stayed up in the bedroom with her. Times I've laid on the bed beside her cot and crept out. Before I ever got to the door she wasn't asleep.
