had a got to be cleaned once a week. And then of course if it was a short day like in the wintertime, you'd got to go and turn all the beds - light all lights in every bedroom and draw all curtains or blinds, whichever they were, when it was dark. And of 
course after that later on you had to go and turn all the beds down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 And did you have to set the table for the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 And serve at that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh and - and afternoon tea and sometimes they'd have people in for tennis at Enfield a
nd I had to carry a great heavy tray ever so far down the garden. Then used to be half a dozen young fellows lounging around and never - never helped you with a tray or said, can I take it or - things were so very different. You know when I think of it, y
ou read in books - I hardly believe it now but then when I think of it it was absolutely true. I don't know.
