\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No. Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3421375\charrsid9714563  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
not unless they had a cold - no, 
they didn't - hot water bottles of course in the winter had to be put in the beds. And - four of the main bedroom had dressing rooms. Well they'd all got brass taps which meant all those taps were cleaned - I'd forgotten that - every day. And they were br
ass.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 There wasn't a nanny or a servant responsible for the children while you were the was there?
