Oh they always had a woman that went with the house, you know what I mean, they used to seem to hire a cottage. And there always seemed to 
be a lady there that well I don't know whether she was the owner or what but she did the - you know, made the beds and did the work. Then we stayed at a hotel in Eastbourne for about a month. I remember. There again I didn't have anything to do at all. Th
a
t's why I went downstairs when Joyce woke up very early one morning and she wanted a bottle and of course it - I went downstairs to find the kitchen and the people were just getting up off the kitchen table - they were sleeping on the table. They were so 
f
ull up. This was a very posh hotel. Right on the end of Terminus Road, we went in there in fact and had our tea there my sister and I about two years ago. I said, this is where I stayed where they slept on the table. They were just getting off. It was a h
uge table, ever so long you know but - of course people used to say they slept in a bath and all sorts of things but I didn't believe it but I know they slept on the table.
