\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 ussy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well I suppose the Vicar or the doctor or - people like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Did you come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
Of course the vicar quite a bit when I - you know, when the children were older because they were in everything and I started going to church again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Why did you think they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well I suppose - well for one thing he was 
in charge of the spiritual side of the parish wasn't he. And of course I suppose they'd had college training and - I don't know whether you'd put their schoolteachers in that category at all. One schoolteacher of Lesleys we got friendly with, he was quite
 nice, but on the other hand I - my brother-in-law was a teacher, they were all - no, I think it would be the vicar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well I wouldn't know. Quite a lot of the children of course went to scho
ol with my boys and they used to go various places, outings and things that were, you know, if there was anything from school they used to go together. Quite a lot of them were tradesmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 s children. But - I knew one tradesman who came to our church who was a church warden, he was a butcher. Oh no, they just - I think, ordinary, they weren't -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 You said that the clergy were looked up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Who did they associate with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well I suppose they'd be their own private friends really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Would they be other clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Probably, yes, of course we wouldn't know that you see what I mean, and their relatives I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 What about teachers? You say your brother-in-law was a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well most of his friends seemed to be teachers. Quite a lot of them were teachers. Three or four of them I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 And employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
No, of course in each case where my husband worked there was terrific - you know, there would be head of his department, there wouldn't be - you know. Wouldn't be like a small firm where there was a head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 What sort of people would you say went to church and to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well I wouldn't know about the chapel people but the church people, they were - oh very much like ourselves. There were quite a 
few teachers and tradesmen used to go. Of course we used to meet them all socially then all of them so they evidently thought they were all very much on a level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living 
or would you say that there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
Oh I think there were different groups. Because some children when my boys went to school seemed to be very, very poor. In fact they had a - a fund from the school, they had a choir and both my boys 
were in it and they used to sing at cinemas before the - the programme started, for a boot fund. Well these kids were given boots. So I think some people must have been very, very poor. And what I can remember, they weren't barefooted exactly but they see
med to be very poorly dressed because if there was anything at school that they wanted costumes for and things like that they didn't seem as though they could buy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 They couldn't afford that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No, and of course I suppose I managed very well - 
I wasn't too badly off but - I made things and - you know, if there was anything, fancy dress at the church or anything I'd make it out of - you see, but a lot of people they're quite - quite unable to do that sort of thing, they buy everything. Of course
 they wouldn't be very well off on five pounds a week where perhaps I should be very well off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 You mean they wouldn't spend their money wisely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 You see, they used to buy such a lot of food, you know, fish and chips and things like that. Well of c
ourse if you cook dinners and that it makes such a difference doesn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
What other groups - you mentioned there were some children you didn't particularly want your boys to play with - would these be in the same group as the ones that were very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Probably. They seemed to be so rough and they used to swear and - you know. In fact there was one murd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 r - you know - the - we've got a road up here. Sidmouth Road, it's been renamed, no I don't think it has, they talk about renaming it. There were
 - it was so bad that people - you could walk through there as a short cut to Francis Road but very, very few people did. They used to sit outside on chairs and on their windowsills, you know the type of place. Very slummy. But now of course a lot of hous
e
s - they had a bomb on it were broken down, were - well, demolished and the council have built a - a place down there now a very nice place, some kind - I don't know what it is quite - a big office down there which has helped. And it's really quite a nice
 little road now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 But in those days that was the rough part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 It was really very, very rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Were there other people who you would say were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No, I think they were mostly very much like ali}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Do you think that one group field itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
I don't really think so. Because when I went to church there was such a lot of, you know, everything was well attended in those days. It was no trouble to - now the working party I belong to now, there's only seven
. There used to be thirty. Well they all seemed to be very much alike. Their husbands had various jobs. There were teachers and all sorts of things you - know but - they seemed to be very much alike in their family life and the children and that because J
ack was in the choir - church choir and I mean their father's were all sorts of things. But they seemed to be very much alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Some families were thought of as rough though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Were others thought of as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Yes. Yes. This
 is - some children I mean were really dirty. And the teachers used to clean their hair - the girls - used to comb their heads and put stuff on their heads. And they really were close to going - well they looked like their father's cut down trousers you k
now, they looked really awful. Well I didn't - I know it was snobbish perhaps but I didn't like - the kid mixing with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 The other group were the respectable ones who kept themselves clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Do you think that these people as a whole would look down on the rough ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No, not really. No I don't think I - of course it was so mixed up the craftsmen and labourers for instance you see my father
 worked on the railway he was a - I suppose you'd put in a labouring class - he wasn't a labourer ex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563 actly but of course there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 engineers and electric - not electricians, don't think were those - anyway, all sorts of craftsmen down there, joiners and th
at. But they all seemed to be more or less - of course I expect they earnt more money - they would but they didn't seem to be a lot of difference in their families you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Not after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3897222 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
, no. Not 'til my husband died and then of course it was a - dreadful struggle because you see, I think I told you the widows pension was such a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 What year was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 1927. The widows pension then was - ten shillings for the widow, five shillings for the eldest child and then three and six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 What difference did it make when your husband was ill or out of work? Was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Not really, no, he was ill for some time after he had pneumonia and of course after that he - he got 
continual attacks of bronchitis. That's when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Was he out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Did he get paid when he was away from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No, not his work. He had sick pay which was little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 How did you manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Well - we had to manag
e the best we could because after pneumonia he had to have new laid eggs and this friend of mine used to go all over the place to get real new laid eggs, and he had to have brandy beaten up in milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Which were expensive things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 But you still managed to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Yes, I managed somehow, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 How often did this happen - that he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 What? Oh never before he had pneumonia. And then it seemed to leave his chest weak but - the Fetter Lane, the Meneer School wanted to
 send him to Egypt to - with a new machine to teach - he'd be out there six months, no, he'd be gone six months and - to teach an Egyptian you see. He would have gone by sea - his life would have been insured for a thousand pounds which was money in those
 days. I would have had a five pound weekly allowance, but he wouldn't go. The doctor said he'd be a new man by the time he got there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Was it before the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh after. Yes, because he was in the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 He was in the Army during the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
Yes. Yes. But he wouldn't go - he wouldn't leave us. I said, well look if you were very ill you'd have to leave us anyway but - no. Anyhow I think it would have taken a week or more to get there by sea, you know, and I mean it would
 have been - the climate was hot and dry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Did you ever gat help from the Guardians, the a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No. Oh I think we had some from his union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 This was after he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 No, when he was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 This was the union of Hono}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 
Yes, it was the - oh dear - no I can't remember what it was called. It was through the union he had to leave the Times and go back to - really, to go back to - Scotland Yard which was less pay. 'Cos I mean it was a - it's not a job I suppose civil S
ervice but - and the hours were l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5312634\charrsid9714563 ong and - the times was a marve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 lous place to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 How long was he at the Times for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Oh about - not much more than a year because all the time he was fighting to stay there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 The union made him go back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 N.A.T. - no, wouldn't be N.A.T.S.O.P.A. would it, not that's the union that - I can't think of the name of the union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 But the union were fighting for him to stay with the Times or to go back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7025548 WR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 Both. It was a different union at the Times but you
 couldn't - he was there about a year and he still hadn't got his union card and - you couldn't - they couldn't employ him longer than that without a card and he couldn't get his card without - oh, I don't know - without working or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15934674 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10303346\charrsid9714563 So it was quite a struggle?
